Checklist for the time when a new version is about to be released:

0.1 Read/revise all the manual (once).
0.2 Check files like README.md, etc.
--
1. Add some functions from file: addthesefunctions 
2. Make some changes from ToDo list. 
--
3.  check spelling.
4.  check examples.
5.  check comments match examples: '<!-- RandomComment -->'.
    --> grep RandomComment *.xml ../lib/*.gd
6.  check version number
7.  check release date.
8.  check citation info.
9.  remove disclaimer in preface.
10.  build the manual.
11.  clean up backup files.
12. commit changes.
13. push to git repository.
14. pull from webpage
    --> make 
15. update webpage
16. alert on yagsnews@xamanek.izt.uam.mx (and others?)